CharacterStyleRange.Content: . The default mode is the image view.

Be sure to always check the road conditions while driving. The Driver Assistance system helps you drive safely and conveniently. Relying solely on the function may cause violation of traffic rules and regulations, resulting in an accident.
Be sure to control the vehicle by your judgment and keep traffic regulations for safety. When the function is active, drive the vehicle with keeping eyes forward and checking the surroundings.
Not all warnings or functions are necessary when they are active, and they do not replace the driver discretion under any circumstances. Stay focused on the road while driving.
Be sure to always check the vehicle surroundings while driving. The equipped cameras and sensors may not operate properly under all driving conditions.
The properties of the Smart Cruise Control system.
: Adjustment of the Smart Cruise Control system settings based on the current drive mode.
To reset the SCC (Smart Cruise Control) settings, press
The properties of the Driving Convenience system.
The Driving Convenience system operates based on the information from the navigation system so you must use the system only when the navigation system operates properly.
: Assistance for driving on motorways according to the set speed and distance while keeping the vehicle centred in the lane.
: Automatic assistance for lane changes when the turn indicator is used while HDA (Motorway Driving Assist) is active.
: Automatic adjustment of the vehicle speed on a motorway based on navigation data.
It operates based on the speed cameras on the route set from the navigation system. To change the guidance settings for speed cameras, on the Home screen, press
The properties of the Speed Limit system.
: Adjusts the vehicle set speed based on the current speed limit of the road.
: Provides a warning when the speed limit is exceeded.
: Display of the current speed limit of the road.
: Disables Speed Limit functions that use the current speed limit.
: Provision of a warning and adjustment of the vehicle's set speed based on the current road's speed limit and the selected offset.
The warning methods for the Driver Assistance systems.
: The volume of the warning sound.
: Activation of the steering wheel vibration warning.
: Deactivation of the Lane Safety audible warning, even if both warning volume and haptic warning are On.
: Lowers all other audio volumes when a driving safety system sounds a warning.
: Lowers all other audio volumes when a parking assist view is active.
The properties of the DAW (Driver Attention Warning) system.
: Notification of the driver when the leading vehicle drives on.
Be sure to always check the road conditions ahead or surroundings before departure. An accident caused by distracted driving can be prevented.
The properties of the Driving Safety system.
: Assistance in collision avoidance. The system provides a warning and actively controls the vehicle when a risk of forward collision is detected.
: The timing of the forward safety system warnings.
: Assistance and warning when risk of forward cross-traffic collision is detected.
: Collision avoidance by provision of a warning and vehicle control when a risk of forward or side collision is detected.
: Automatic adjustment of the steering wheel to keep the vehicle within the boundaries of its lane.
: Display of blind spot view in the cluster when changing the lanes using the turn indicator.
: Warning on detection of a risk of blind-spot collision, and automatic vehicle control while departing a parallel parking spot.
: Provision of a warning and door control when a risk of blind-spot collision is detected while exiting the vehicle.
Properties of the Parking Safety systems.
: Automatic activation of the surround view monitor when the parking distance warning is active.
: Automatic activation of PDW (Parking Distance Warning) at low speeds.
: Provision of a warning and vehicle control when a risk of collision is detected while reversing.
: Provision of a warning and vehicle control when a risk of rear cross-traffic collision is detected while reversing.

Even if your vehicle is equipped with a driver assistance system, always check for objects around the vehicle when driving or parking. Relying on the Parking Safety system may cause an accident. Accordingly, be sure to control the vehicle by your judgment.
When the sensors cannot detect any obstacles due to the detection limit, it may cause an accident. Be sure to always check the surroundings while parking.
You can change the vehicle settings for driving conditions.

CharacterStyleRange.Content: Available settings may differ depending on the vehicle model and specifications.
Personalised CUSTOM drive mode based on user selections.
: A customised drive mode based on user selections for each of the systems, which influence the driving experience.
Automatic selection of the brake mode (feel, responsiveness, etc.) optimised for your driving style.
A change of the drive mode is shown by a detailed image of the vehicle.
This function maintains the driving performance and estimates the distance to empty (DTE) when connecting a trailer.
Decrease the energy consumption by reducing the heating and cooling power of the climate control system.
A synthetic driving sound for EVs. Please select a volume.
You can configure the operation environment for climate control system.

CharacterStyleRange.Content: Available settings may differ depending on the vehicle model and specifications.
Blocking of outside air intake into the vehicle cabin.
: Washer fluid scent is automatically prevented from entering the cabin.
: Automatic closing of windows and activation of internal air circulation upon entering a tunne
Automatic switching to outside (fresh) air ventilation to decrease humidity after an extended use of internal air circulation.
: Automatic switching to outside (fresh) air ventilation to decrease humidity after an extended use of internal air circulation.
The air conditioner is automatically operated to create a flow of air to clear the windscreen.
: Activation of fresh air ventilation and A/C to remove windshield moisture quickly.
: Automatic activation of the climate system to prevent fog on the windscreen.
: After the vehicle is turned Off, the fan will run automatically to dry the inside of the air conditioner to prevent mold growth.
: Disabling of rear seat air condition controls.
: Automatic deactivation of the rear climate system when no occupants are detected in the rear seats.
: Decrease the energy consumption by reducing the heating and cooling power of the climate control system.
: The touch function will operate only on a part of the climate touchscreen.
Activate/adjust steering wheel and driver seat warmer/ventilation based on climate settings.
: Steering wheel warmer adjusts automatically based on climate settings.
: Driver seat warmer/ventilation adjusts automatically based on climate settings.
You can set to use various features (motions and warmer control for the driver's seat, rear seat, and steering wheel) that are related to the seats and steering wheel.

CharacterStyleRange.Content: Available settings may differ depending on the vehicle model and specifications.
Activate/adjust steering wheel and driver seat warmer/ventilation based on climate settings.
: Steering wheel warmer adjusts automatically based on climate settings.
: Driver seat warmer/ventilation adjusts automatically based on climate settings.
The seat and steering wheel are automatically moved when the driver and passenger enter or exit the vehicle.
: Turns off the feature where the driver seat automatically moves when the driver enters/exits the vehicle.
: The passenger seat is automatically moved when the passenger enters or exits the vehicle.
: The left rear seat is automatically moved when the passenger exits the vehicle.
: The right rear seat is automatically moved when the passenger exits the vehicle.
: The steering wheel is automatically moved when the driver enters or exits the vehicle.
Display of information on the changing of the seat position.
Recommendation of a posture that fits the driver's body type and provision of a clinical analysis for back health.
Ergo-motion seat movements are utilised to reduce fatigue, support driver comfort, and increase driver awareness and safety.
: Comfortable stretch options that use seat movements to help reduce body fatigue.
: Assistance in maintaining a comfortable posture by adjusting the hips and waist after 1 hour of driving.
: The Lumbar Stabilisation System decreases pressure on the lumbar spine and reduces back discomfort while driving.
You can configure the settings for vehicle lights.

CharacterStyleRange.Content: Available settings may differ depending on the vehicle model and specifications.
Setting of the vehicle cabin's mood lighting.
: Adjust the brightness of the cabin's mood lighting.
: Adjusts the colour of the ambient light.
: The colour of the mood lighting changes according to the selected drive mode.
: Automatic dimming of the mood lighting under darkened conditions.
: When a speed alert is provided by the navigation system, the mood lighting flashes.
: The brightness of the ambient lighting is adjusted based on the vehicle speed.
Definition of the number of times the turn indicator blinks when the lever is moved slightly.
The condition under which the outside mirrors will unfold and the puddle or door handle lights will turn on automatically.
When the ignition is turned Off, the tail lamps and head lamps turn off after approximately 15 seconds.
The type of lighting to be used for the dynamic welcome light. The selected pattern will be applied at the next vehicle start-up.
Assistance in reducing high beam glare to oncoming vehicles.
The speed at which the intelligent headlights (high beams) activate. (Beams will adjust to prevent blinding nearby vehicles.)
Illumination of the interior buttons and switches at all times.
You can configure the operation environment for the tailgate and doors.

CharacterStyleRange.Content: Available settings may differ depending on the vehicle model and specifications.
Definition of a condition for all doors to be locked automatically.
Definition of a condition for all doors to be unlocked automatically.
All doors are unlocked when the unlock button is pressed twice. (Single press unlocks driver door only)
Press [Power Tailgate] to automatically open or close the boot.
Definition of the Power Tailgate opening and closing speed.
The height, the power tailgate automatically moves on opening.
The tailgate will be automatically opened when approaching the tailgate with the Smart Key.
Enable/disable the remote window control function.
Register a digital key to your smartphone or an NFC-enabled key card, to use the smartphone or card as a smart key.

: An alert is displayed when a specified service interval is due.

: Enter the service interval reminder time.
To initialize all service interval reminder settings, press
Alert on detection of movement in the passenger compartment after the vehicle is locked.
Wireless charging system for mobile devices
Choose the indicator display type when a mobile phone is being charged using the wireless charging pad.
Rear wiper will automatically wipe if the front wipers are On and the gear position is in reverse.
The rear view camera image is displayed
The level of tinting for the vehicle's glass panes.
This function maintains the driving performance and estimates the distance to empty (DTE) when connecting a trailer.
Things to check before using the trailer.

The settings for the advanced sound system.
Delivers improved soundstage and dynamics for compressed file formats.
Monitors the vehicle speed and automatically adjusts aspects of the music to ensure a consistent listening experience.
This technology converts stereo sources to offer an immersive audio experience, with sound effects that allow the occupants to feel that they are in a real concert hall.
To reset all audio settings to the default values, press
Adaptive processing to ensure a consistent experience in all driving conditions.
The volume is automatically adjusted to the vehicle speed.
Automatic lowering of audio volumes when starting the system, if they are higher than the defined maximum. Only applies, if the vehicle was Off for a certain period of time.

CharacterStyleRange.Content: Phone projection is linked to the Bluetooth sound effect settings.
You can set different sound effects for each broadcast or media mode.
This option is not provided in sound settings.

BOSE's latest surround technology that upmixes stereo sources to deliver a vivid, immersive listening experience. Centerpoint 360 optimally positions instrumental sounds in the cabin by finely shifting sounds. This offers a realistic sound stage, allowing all occupants to fe
el that they are on stage.
This feature does not work for multi-channel (e.g., 5.1ch) media sources.

It is a technology that converts a stereo source and provides a sense of presence and immersive so that make you feel a part of the performance. It provides three sound effects modes by reconstructing characteristics through each extracted source.
: A sound stage unfolds in front of the vehicle with a clear vocal image.
: Delivers immersive sound that fills the entire vehicle space.
: Customizes the position of the vocal image and the level of immersion.

CharacterStyleRange.Content: Adjust the volume levels for individual system features or initialise all volume settings.
To initialise all system sound settings, press
: Set the distance to a camera, at which the alert will be triggered.
Playing of route guidance prompts during phone calls.
Lowering of audio volumes when navigation prompts are played. This may not work for phone projection media.
Pressing the mute button on the steering wheel while navigation prompts are playing, will mute the guidance for 10 seconds.
A synthetic driving sound for EVs. Please select a volume.
The warning methods for the Driver Assistance systems.
The volume of the warning sound.
Activation of the steering wheel vibration warning.
Deactivation of the Lane Safety audible warning, even if both warning volume and haptic warning are On.
Lowers all other audio volumes when a driving safety system sounds a warning.
Lowers all other audio volumes when a parking assist view is active.
The volume levels of each function when using a phone projection app.
Adjustment of the Android Auto volume.
To initialise all system sound settings for phone projection, press
Adjustment of the Apple CarPlay volume.
To initialise all system sound settings for phone projection, press

Manage Bluetooth devices or configure their operation settings. You can also activate the phone projection so that you can control the smartphone App from the system screen after connecting the smartphone to the system.
Available settings may differ depending on the vehicle model and specifications.
The device connection settings screen appears.

CharacterStyleRange.Content: Select the theme to be used in the cluster display.
: Cluster theme is automatically selected based on drive mode.
: The style/appearance of the gauges shown in the cluster.
: The style/type of graphics used in the cluster.
Select the contents to be shown in the cluster display.
: Provision of a pop-up when wipers or lights are activated.
: Display of traffic information such as speed limits.
: Provision of a warning in case of icy conditions, i.e. when the outside temperature is below 4°C (39°F).
: Display of blind spot view in the cluster when changing the lanes using the turn indicator.
A greeting chime is provided when the cluster is turned On or Off.
Configure settings for the head-up display, which displays information such as driving speed and road-related information while driving.
Information will be displayed on the windscreen.
Adjust the height, rotation, and brightness of the head-up display.
Automatically save head-up display height and rotation settings
: Auto saving of height and rotation of the head-up display set by the driver to the Integrated Memory System.
Selectively turn on or off the information displayed on the heads-up display.
Subscribe to the Kia Connect service or see the modem information.
Available settings may differ depending on the vehicle model and specifications.
The Kia Connect settings screen appears.

CharacterStyleRange.Content: For details on how to update the system software using a USB storage device, refer to the following:
For details on how to update the system software via a wireless connection, refer to the following:
Shows the latest system update information.
After update is completed, the system will display the main update items on the screen. Scan the QR code to view the update announcement.
Shows the modem information for use of the Kia Connect service.
Time is automatically set using GPS (based on the vehicle location) or the network.
Manually change the date and time settings. Disable
and before manually changing the date and time settings.
Change the system time display format.
Displays the system time in the format of daylight savings time.
The language used for the system.
Once the language has been changed, it takes a while to apply the new languag

e to the system. The notification pop-up window appears as soon as the new language is applied to the system. After a short wait or pressing anywhere outside the pop-up window, the window automatically disappears.
Changing the system language does not affect the display of other unique data such as MP3 music file name.
Depending on the system language, the Bluetooth phone message view and voice recognition may not be supported.
The keyboard used in the system.
Voice dictation is automatically activated when entering the keyboard screen.
Voice recognition is supported only for certain languages. If you change the system language, voice recognition may not be supported.
The measurement units used in the system.
Select the units for distance and vehicle speed to display on the screen.
Select the unit for temperature to display on the screen.
Select the unit for fuel (energy) economy to display on the screen.
The displayed name may differ depending on the vehicle model and specifications.
The displayed unit for fuel economy may differ depending on the vehicle fuel type.
Select the unit for tyre pressure to display on the screen.
Media will not turn On automatically at vehicle start-up.
Infotainment remains On when the vehicle is turned Off.
When the vehicle is turned Off, the infotainment system remains On for a given length of time, or until the driver's door is opened.
Reset the information of the account currently logged in, or reset all accounts.
You can also reset all settings for the login profile.
